- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses parallel programming models and communication protocols for a many-core architecture. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the Adapteva Epiphany architecture and its physical topology. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper discusses the energy efficiency and scalability of the Epiphany architecture. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper discusses parallel programming models and their implementation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the development of an OpenSHMEM implementation for a specific hardware system.
